.SH NAME
XMLHttpRequest.open \- XMLHttpRequest: open() method
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]Note:\f[R] This feature is available in Web Workers, except for
Service Workers.
.PP
The \f[CR]XMLHttpRequest\f[R] method \f[B]\f[CB]open()\f[B]\f[R]
initializes a newly\-created request, or re\-initializes an existing
one.
.RS
.PP
\f[B]Note:\f[R] Calling this method for an already active request (one
for which \f[CR]open()\f[R] has already been called) is the equivalent
of calling \f[CR]abort()\f[R].
.RE
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
open(method, url)
open(method, url, async)
open(method, url, async, user)
open(method, url, async, user, password)
.EE
.SS Parameters
.TP
\f[B]method\f[R]
The HTTP request method to use, such as \f[CR]\[dq]GET\[dq]\f[R],
\f[CR]\[dq]POST\[dq]\f[R], \f[CR]\[dq]PUT\[dq]\f[R],
\f[CR]\[dq]DELETE\[dq]\f[R], etc.
Ignored for non\-HTTP(S) URLs.
.TP
\f[B]url\f[R]
A string or any other object with a stringifier \[em] including a
\f[CR]URL\f[R] object \[em] that provides the URL of the resource to
send the request to.
.TP
\f[B]async\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
An optional Boolean parameter, defaulting to \f[CR]true\f[R], indicating
whether or not to perform the operation asynchronously.
If this value is \f[CR]false\f[R], the \f[CR]send()\f[R] method does not
return until the response is received.
If \f[CR]true\f[R], notification of a completed transaction is provided
using event listeners.
This \f[I]must\f[R] be true if the \f[CR]multipart\f[R] attribute is
\f[CR]true\f[R], or an exception will be thrown.
.RS
.RS
.PP
\f[B]Note:\f[R] Synchronous requests on the main thread can be easily
disruptive to the user experience and should be avoided; in fact, many
browsers have deprecated synchronous XHR support on the main thread
entirely.
Synchronous requests are permitted in \f[CR]Worker\f[R]s.
.RE
.RE
.TP
\f[B]user\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
The optional user name to use for authentication purposes; by default,
this is the \f[CR]null\f[R] value.
.TP
\f[B]password\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
The optional password to use for authentication purposes; by default,
this is the \f[CR]null\f[R] value.
